        <h1>LeetCode 2221: Find Triangular Sum of an Array (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a 0-indexed integer array nums, where nums[i] is a digit between 0 and 9 (inclusive). The triangular sum of nums is found by repeatedly creating a new array where each element is the sum of adjacent pairs modulo 10, until only one element remains. Return the triangular sum of nums.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3,4,5]<br>
                Output: 8<br>
                Explanation: [1,2,3,4,5] → [3,5,7,9] → [8,2,6] → [0,8] → [8]
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int triangularSum(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        
        // Process the array level by level, reducing size by 1 each iteration
        // Start from n-1 and work down to 1
        for (int len = n - 1; len &gt; 0; len--) {
            // For each level, calculate new values by summing adjacent pairs
            for (int i = 0; i &lt; len; i++) {
                // Add current element with next element and take modulo 10
                // Store result in-place by overwriting the left element
                nums[i] = (nums[i] + nums[i + 1]) % 10;
            }
        }
        
        // After all iterations, the result is stored in the first element
        return nums[0];
    }
};</code></pre>
